main event: A witness observed a bright silver round object that was about 50 times the size of a star in Manitowish Waters, Wisconsin on March 8, 1956.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for approximately 15 to 20 minutes,The object moved erratically at angles of 20 degrees and 90 degrees before disappearing from view,There was no radar contact detected for the object,The sighting might involve careful analysis to determine if the object was Venus or another celestial body,The observer reported the object as having a bright silver color.
sighted object: one round object, bright silver in color
witness description: a hardware store owner and a school teacher
